<topic id='business_definition_pharmacist.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Pharmacist - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pharmacist">Pharmacist</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
 who is registered with the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">GPhC</xref>).        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pharmacist">Pharmacist</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
 who is licensed to prepare and dispense medicines.        </p>
    <p>
In order for 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pharmacist">Pharmacists</xref>
 to practise in Great Britain they must be registered with the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">GPhC</xref>) and must renew their registration annually.        </p>
    <p>
Once a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pharmacist">Pharmacist</xref>
 registers with the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>, they are allocated a registration number which uniquely identifies each registered 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pharmacist">Pharmacist</xref>. This registration number is a 7 digit number starting with the number 2.        </p>
    <p>
All 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pharmacist">Pharmacists</xref>
 who are currently licensed to practise in Great Britain are listed on the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council_register">General Pharmaceutical Council Register</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
